President of the National Funeral Practitioners Association, Muzi Hlengwa speaks to eNCA. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Over 3,000 funeral industry employees are expected to down tools from Monday. They have vowed not to collect corpses after the government failed to respond to their demands. READ: COVID-19: Funeral homes running out of room Funeral parlour directors are demanding the outsourcing of mortuary facilities to be recognised and legalised. They also want the amendment of by-laws by municipalities to enable cluster storages.